explanation: We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We maintain a dp array where dp[mask] represents the maximum stability of a spanning tree that includes all nodes represented by the mask. We iterate over all possible masks and for each mask, we iterate over all nodes and their neighbors. If a node is included in the mask, we update the dp value by considering the minimum strength of the edges. If a node is not included in the mask and it has an optional edge, we update the dp value by considering the minimum strength of the edges after upgrading the edge. Finally, we return the maximum stability of all possible spanning trees.

